====***Test Cases***====

1) To check the help message using --help command
2) To check the help message using --h command
3) To check  addition calucation by passing possitive numbers
4) To check  addition calucation by passing Negative numbers
5) To check  subtraction calucation by passing possitive numbers
6) To check  subtraction calucation by passing Negative numbers
7) To check  Multiply calucation by passing possitive numbers
8) To check  Multiply calucation by passing negative numbers
9) To check  Multiply calucation by passing one negative and one possitive number
10) To check  Divison calucation by passing possitive numbers
11)To check  Division calucation by passing negative numbers
12)To check  Division calucation by passing zero number


***** Manual testing *****

1.To check the help message using --help command

 python .\calculator.py --help
usage: calculator.py [-h] [--operation {add,subtract,multiply,divide}] num1 num2

Simple command-line calculator

positional arguments:
  num1                  First number
  num2                  Second number

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --operation {add,subtract,multiply,divide}
                        Operation to perform (default: add)


2.To check the help message using --h command

 python .\calculator.py --h
usage: calculator.py [-h] [--operation {add,subtract,multiply,divide}] num1 num2

Simple command-line calculator

positional arguments:
  num1                  First number
  num2                  Second number

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --operation {add,subtract,multiply,divide}
                        Operation to perform (default: add)


3. To check  addition calucation by passing possitive numbers

   python .\calculator.py --operation add 25 25
   Result: 50.0

4. To check  addition calucation by passing Negative numbers

    python .\calculator.py --operation add -10 -12
    Result: -22.0

5.To check  subtraction calucation by passing possitive numbers

   python .\calculator.py --operation subtract 24 12
   Result: 12.0

6.To check  subtraction calucation by passing Negative numbers

    python .\calculator.py --operation subtract -24 -12
    Result: -12.0

7. To check  Multiply calucation by passing possitive numbers

        python .\calculator.py --operation multiply 19 2
        Result: 38.0

8.  To check  Multiply calucation by passing negative numbers

          python .\calculator.py --operation multiply -11 -2
          Result: 22.0

9.  To check  Multiply calucation by passing one possitivi and one negative number

         python .\calculator.py --operation multiply -11 2
         Result: -22.0

10.To check  Divison calucation by passing possitive numbers
        python .\calculator.py --operation divide 30 15
        Result: 2.0

11.To check  Division calucation by passing negative numbers
         python .\calculator.py --operation divide -12 -10
         Result: 1.2

12.To check  Division calucation by passing zero number
        python .\calculator.py --operation divide 12 0
        Error: Division by zero

13.To check more than one oprations at a time
       python .\calculator.py --operation add 12 10 --operation subtract 10 5
       usage: calculator.py [-h] [--operation {add,subtract,multiply,divide}] num1 num2
       calculator.py: error: unrecognized arguments: 10 5